

The numbers are placed on the usual Ulam spiral  

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
5&4&3\\[2pt]
6&1&2\\[2pt]
7&8&9
\end{array}
\]

which grows outward clockwise (right → up → left → down).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.  Locate \(2026\) on the grid

For a point \((x,y)\) the “layer’’ (or ring) is  

\[
k=\max\{|x|,|y|\},
\qquad s=2k+1\;( \text{side‑length}),\qquad
M=s^{2}\;( \text{largest number in that layer}).
\]

Since \(45^{2}=2025<2026<47^{2}=2209\), the number \(2026\) lies in the layer  

\[
k=23,\qquad s=47,\qquad M=47^{2}=2209 .
\]

The first number of this layer is the previous maximum plus 1:

\[
2025+1=2026,
\]

and it is placed at  

\[
(k,\,-(k-1))=(23,-22).
\]

Thus  

\[
\boxed{2026\text{ is at }(23,-22)} .
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.  Coordinates of the eight neighbours

The 8 surrounding cells are  

\[
\begin{array}{ccl}
\text{U}:&(23,-21) &\qquad\text{D}:&(23,-23)\\[2pt]
\text{L}:&(22,-22) &\qquad\text{R}:&(24,-22)\\[2pt]
\text{UL}:&(22,-21) &\qquad\text{UR}:&(24,-21)\\[2pt]
\text{DL}:&(22,-23) &\qquad\text{DR}:&(24,-23)
\end{array}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3.  Value at a given coordinate

For a point in layer \(k\)

* if it is on the **right side** \((x=k,\;y\ge -k+1)\):
  \[
  n = \bigl[(2k-1)^{2}+1\bigr] + y + (k-1).
  \]

* if it is the **bottom‑right corner** \((k,-k)\):
  \[
  n = (2k+1)^{2}.
  \]

* if it is on the **bottom side** \((y=-k,\;x\ge -k)\):
  \[
  n = (2k+1)^{2} - (k-x).
  \]

* similarly for the other sides (top, left, top‑right, etc.).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4.  Evaluate the eight neighbours

| coordinate | layer \(k\) | side | value |
|------------|-------------|------|-------|
| (23,‑21)   | 23 | right side | \(2026+1=2027\) |
| (23,‑23)   | 23 | bottom‑right corner | \(47^{2}=2209\) |
| (22,‑22)   | 22 | bottom‑right corner | \(45^{2}=2025\) |
| (24,‑22)   | 24 | right side | \(2210+1=2211\) |
| (22,‑21)   | 22 | right side (first of layer) | \(1849+1=1850\) |
| (24,‑21)   | 24 | right side | \(2210+2=2212\) |
| (22,‑23)   | 23 | bottom side | \(2209-1=2208\) |
| (24,‑23)   | 24 | right side (first of layer) | \(2210\) |

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5.  Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
\Sigma &=2027+2209+2025+2211+1850+2212+2208+2210\\
      &=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
----
